The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for ensemble learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the use of evolutionary algorithms for building diverse ensembles of classifiers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of a new fitness function and selection criterion, which are related to optimization and search, respectively, suggesting that the paper could also be classified under cs.DM (Data Mining) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
